@node I_Introduction "IdentifyBB2/Introduction"
@prev main
@next I_Requirements

               @{FG "highlight"}Introduction@{FG "Text"}

     @{b}Identify library@{ub} is an Amiga shared library by @{i}Richard Koerber@{ui}. This 
     library is mostly used when you want to know more about any Amiga
     system (and not only...). In fact, identify library provides four 
     functions to detect hardware features, Zorro I/II/III boards, getting Alert's
     human-readable explanations and the name of a particular function
     provided by any Amiga shared library.

     For more informations about the Identify library, please read 
     Identify's Autodoc.

     The pourpose of this archive is to provide some useful files for all
     @{b}Blitz Basic 2@{ub} programmers that want to use Identify library
     in their programs.

     You can find a @{"tutorial" link I_Tutorial} section too. 

@endnode

